adviseScripts.text: Heya!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: What do you want for lunch today?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I'm in the mood for meat.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Let's have beef-flavored Nutrium.
Let's have lamb-flavored Nutrium.
Be-beef flavored?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: You know I'm a fiend for beef,
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: but I had that for dinner last night.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Lamb-flavored?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I've never tried it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: As long as it's meat, I'm sure it'll be good.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Let's get a move on, I'm starving!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Jackal and I talk about the current meat flavors that are available.
Shooting guns is a blast!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: When you pull that trigger and then... kablam!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Everything shatters into a million pieces! It's the coolest.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Just make sure you don't shoot at people.
It's rather reckless of you to fire so indiscriminately.
Yeah, yeah, I know. The Captain already told me not to.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: She explicitly forbade it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Unless she gives me a signal, that is.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Aw c'mon, it's fun.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: You don't want me to have fun?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I spend time with Jackal perusing through the latest gun catalogue.
Commander? My tooth hurts.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: This has never happened before, it's weird.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: What? We better get you to the hospital right away.
You didn't bite down on a stone by any chance, did you?
Absolutely not. I detest hospitals.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: It's haunted by some ghost that walks around with its eyes closed. It freaks me out!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: How did you know?! I was munching on some stones this morning, but it backfired on me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: You must be clairvoyant or something!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I lecture Jackal about the importance of proper dental hygiene.
A couple of days ago at the store, I saw a necklace I really liked.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I decided to take it with me, but the A.C.P.U. followed me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: What's the big deal? I was so scared I ended up having to run away.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: They went after you because stealing is illegal.
They just wanted to give you a hard time.
Stealing? What's that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: ... Oh, right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I do seem to remember the Captain telling me not to take things I want from the store.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Ugh!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Why must those morons always pester me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: They're always busting my hump and trying to capture me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Jackal about necklaces she likes.
The A.C.P.U. is the absolute worst!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Whenever I run into them, they always give me a hard time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: What did I ever do to them?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: It's impossible to be liked by everyone.
It's not entirely unreasonable for the police to feel the way they do about you.
Yeah, you're right. Besides, I don't like them either!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Fine by me. We can just go on hating each other.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: What does their being the police have to do with me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I spend time listening to Jackal talk behind A.C.P.U's back.
Get this. I gave some dude a thrashing a while back.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Today, I'm relaxing, minding my own business, and suddenly his brother comes up to me all in a huff.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Why's he so mad at me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Imagine if Viper got beat up by someone.
Imagine if Crow got beat up by someone.
If Viper got beat up...
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Then that's just how it is. Why would I get upset over that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: If the Captain got beat up...
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I'd want to know who did it! Then I'd find them and...
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: ... Oh, so that's how that guy felt today.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I begin to explain to Jackal how to enact revenge, then decide against it.
The Captain is so amazing. She knows everything.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: That's why she commands respect from everyone, including me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: What about me?
You're pretty amazing yourself, Jackal.
You're amazing too, Commander!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: But between the two of you, I'd say the winner is...
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: ... aw heck, I can't decide! Either way, you're both winners in my book.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: As if!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: People always say that I'm useless.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Except Captain and Viper, of course, but everyone else says so.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Jackal as she showers compliments on Crow.
*chomp* *chomp*
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Hey, you want some of this?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I came by this yesterday, and it's not half bad.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Sorry, I don't think my teeth are up to the task.
Sure, but I'll melt it down first.
You sure?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: If so, then more for me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: ... You're really not eating?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I wonder what it tastes like when it's melted...
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I wanna try that too!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Jackal gives me more pointers on how to choose delicious dishes.
There's this giant wall that separates my neighborhood from the Ark.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: It's a real pain in the butt to move around, and it's next to impossible to jump over.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Got any bright ideas on how I can get around it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Let's practice jumping over it.
I'll tear that wall down.
Good idea!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Since we won't be able to get rid of the wall, I might as well try and learn to jump higher.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Hehe! I'm gonna start practicing straight away!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Ha, you can't be serious!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Not even the Captain could tear down such an imposing wall.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Jackal and I practice how to add some height to our jumps.
Nothing beats running around!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: But Captain never lets me run around in the hideout.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Why doesn't she let me do what I want?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Probably because it makes a lot of noise.
The hideout is much too small for you to run around in.
Noise? What's wrong with noise?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I like noise!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: That's why I run around in the first place!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I guess you're right... our hideout isn't exactly a sprawling estate.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: The Captain is so thoughtful! She always has my best interests in mind.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I run around with Jackal.
Cmndr. Lik cmdfn.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I can't understand a word she's saying when she's gnawing on something.
Cmndr?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Still can't make out what you're saying, but... thanks?
Think you could drop what you're holding in your mouth first?
Hehe! Hehehe!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: IUf Cmnder is hppy, I'm happy!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Hehe! Hehehe!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: *spit*
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: *thud*
It's a grenade!
The Captain told me to give this to you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Don't worry, the pin's still in it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I teach Jackal how to use the message system.
Commander!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Pat me on the head!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: 10 times. No! 100 times!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: You sure you won't get tired of it?
How does 1,000 times sound?
Trust me, I'll be fine.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: So pat away!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I love it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I spend time patting Jackal's head.
Apparently a jackal is a type of animal?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Why would they name me after an animal?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Because you like meat?
Because you're cute and cuddly?
I am a dyed-in-the-wool carnivore, no doubt about that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: And animals like meat too...
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: So that's why I'm called Jackal! It all makes sense now!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Cute... and cuddly?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Is that supposed to be some kind of insult?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: You better watch yourself, or else I'm going to get mad.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Jackal and I watch a nature documentary about animal life.
I wanna pull a prank on the A.C.P.U.!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: They're always on my case, so it's time I gave them a taste of their own medicine.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Got any good prank ideas?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Get on their nerves, then run away.
Just lay low and keep quiet.
You call that a prank? Sounds to me like that's just being immature.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: That way, the A.C.P.U. won't have any reason to bother me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: They won't even know what hit 'em!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I look up additional ideas for pranks.
Viper often goes to get her nails done.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: They're always so shiny and pretty.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I want to try it too!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: How about getting your teeth treated?
You want to get your nails done?
My teeth?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Ooooh, then they'd be super shiny!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: That'd be awesome! I love it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Sure, why not?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: But wait a minute... that'd mean I'd have to walk around with my gloves off.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: On second thought, I don't want to.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I tell Jackal the importance of pampering oneself occasionally.
I caught the guy who caused that commotion a couple days ago, but he keeps denying everything.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: All he does is keep repeating "I don't know" ad nauseum.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: What should I do to make him fess up?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Ask him politely.
Maybe he really doesn't know anything.
Ask politely?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Why would I do that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Wouldn't it be faster to just smack him around a bit?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Maybe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Actually, now that I think about it, he may not have as much to do with this as I originally thought.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I guess I'll release him. I'm sure he'd appreciate it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Jackal and I read up on how to properly address a line of questioning.

Commander.
Is money important?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Whenever I question anyone who's committed a crime,
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: they say they did it because they needed money.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: So I'm curious: is money really that important?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: It's not that important.
It's incredibly important.
That's what I figured.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I know you use it to buy food and stuff like that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: But I don't see what the big deal about money is when you can just steal what you want.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: So you agree with them?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: In that case, what's to stop you from stabbing us in the back and pawning off all our belongings?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: That's something a person who was mad about money would do.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I teach Jackal how to count money.
This necklace is digging into my neck.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I'm gonna take it off.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Won't that upset Crow?
Don't take it off. It looks good on you.
The Captain?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: She's never gotten sore at me for something like that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Just to be safe though, I'll run it by her first.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: You think so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Hehehe!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I'll leave it on then.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Jackal and I look at more necklaces online for her to buy.
I dig our little neighborhood.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I like it because there are a lot of places to run around, and a ton of things to break!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I don't know why everyone else is so down on it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: They're just jealous.
Because this place is dangerous for ordinary people.
Jealous?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I suppose you've got a point. The Ark is so small, and the A.C.P.U. is always on your case if you break anything.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I feel bad for people living in the Ark.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: What are you talking about?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: There's nothing dangerous at all about our neighborhood.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Jackal go on bragging about the Outer Rim.
The Captain is always reading a book or watching a movie.
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I don't get it. Books or movies don't fill your stomach, so what's the point?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: They may not fill your stomach, but they can enrich your mind.
She probably thinks it makes her look cool.
It does what to your mind?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Enrich? What's that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Are you saying the Captain actually eats those books and movies?
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: Well, if you ask me,
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I'd say she's succeeded!
adviseScripts.speaker: Jackal

adviseScripts.text: I try to recommend books and movies to Jackal, but give up.
